article.description: Tamika Catchings scored 23 points to lead Indiana past the Washington Mystics 67-57 Thursday night, securing the Fever's first playoff berth in three years.
article.headline: Fever in playoffs with win over Mystics
article.linkText: Fever clinch playoff spot with win over Mystics
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Tamika Catchings made sure the Indiana Fever
didn't have a chance to fall out of the WNBA playoff race in the
final week of the season for a third straight year.

Catchings scored 23 points on 9-for-11 shooting, and the Fever
(18-12) clinched their first postseason berth since 2002 with a
67-57 win over the Washington Mystics on Thursday night.

"Tamika didn't force things tonight," Indiana coach Brian
Winters said. "She plays great games, even when she doesn't shoot.
When she shoots, that's even a bonus."

Natalie Williams had 15 points and Kelly Miller added 13 for the
Fever, who set a franchise mark for home wins with 12.

Catchings also had two key offensive rebounds in the final two
minutes, keeping possessions alive and burning valuable time off
the clock.

"If I can get rebounds and help this team, that's what it's
going to be," Catchings said.

With four games remaining in the regular season, the Fever moved
one game ahead of the idle New York Liberty for second place and
homecourt advantage in the first round of the playoffs.

Indiana shot 51 percent from the field, and limited Washington
to 38 percent.

Chastity Melvin had 20 points and 10 rebounds, and DeLisha
Milton-Jones added 20 points Washington (14-16).

"Tamika Catchings proved she is one of the best," Mystics
coach Richie Adubato said. "She made the big, clutch plays."

Indiana opened the game with a 7-0 run and never trailed.
Williams and Miller scored four points each as the Fever went on a
10-2 run in the second half to stretch their lead to 50-37 with
12:42 to play.
